article.headline: Campbell 93, Gardner-Webb 73
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Jonathan Rodriguez scored 26 points and grabbed 15 rebounds to lead Campbell to a 93-73 victory over Gardner-Webb on Friday night. Jake Wohlfeil had 19 points, Reggie Bishop, 15 and Kyle Vejraska, 13 for the Camels (8-9, 3-2 A-Sun). Rodriguez had 18 points in the opening period as the Camels built a 52-34 halftime lead, closing the first half on a 16-3 run. Gardner-Webb (8-11, 2-3) cut the lead to eight at 72-64 with 7:40 left, but the Camels closed on a 21-9 run to get the win. Thomas Sanders led Gardner-Webb with 24 points, and Grayson Flittner had 18. Aaron Linn scored 11 points. Campbell held the Bulldogs to just 37.9 percent (11-29) shooting in the opening half and 43.1 percent (25-58) for the game.
